WEBVTT

01:04.472 --> 01:05.670
Hey.

01:05.706 --> 01:07.372
Who's that?

01:08.534 --> 01:09.869
You can trust him.

01:12.876 --> 01:14.849
The uh,

01:14.884 --> 01:15.705
the place is under
construction,

01:15.741 --> 01:18.284
so don't worry about any alarms.

01:19.978 --> 01:22.754
If I hear anything go out
on the radio,

01:22.790 --> 01:25.086
I'll head it off.

02:22.809 --> 02:24.977
I got a bad feeling about this,
man.

02:26.955 --> 02:28.689
Didn't Frank pass in this job?

02:28.724 --> 02:30.422
I need the money, Kevin.

02:32.759 --> 02:33.659
We're in.

02:33.694 --> 02:35.486
Let's go.

03:38.483 --> 03:40.294
Jackpot!

03:41.830 --> 03:43.726
That's what we came for.

03:52.071 --> 03:53.868
What the fuck is that?

03:58.143 --> 04:00.707
It's a motion sensor.

04:00.743 --> 04:01.713
<i>DISPATCH OFFICER 1 :</i>
<i>43-17.</i>

04:01.748 --> 04:02.908
<i>43-18.</i>

04:02.943 --> 04:04.543
<i>Possible Code 5 burglary</i>
<i>in progress</i>

04:04.578 --> 04:05.380
<i>at the Cash House.</i>

04:05.415 --> 04:06.412
<i>Any units in the vicinity?</i>

04:06.448 --> 04:07.484
What do we do now?

04:07.520 --> 04:09.416
If a call went out,
I'm sure Zwick got it.

04:09.451 --> 04:10.249
I can't get caught, man.

04:10.284 --> 04:11.150
April...

04:11.185 --> 04:12.256
I'm all she got.
What-- what do we do?

04:12.291 --> 04:14.125
Kev--
Kev, it's gonna be okay.

04:14.160 --> 04:15.554
Your sister's gonna be fine.

04:15.589 --> 04:16.757
But let's get a move on.

04:16.792 --> 04:18.863
Pack up that stuff
and take it to the van.

04:18.899 --> 04:19.957
I got this.

04:19.993 --> 04:22.428
Dispatch, this is DC 11,
I'm in the area.

04:22.463 --> 04:24.864
I'll swing by.

04:24.899 --> 04:26.003
<i>OFFICER 1 :</i>
<i>4317, copy?</i>

04:26.039 --> 04:28.666
<i>I'm almost 97th.</i>

04:28.701 --> 04:29.607
<i>Three minutes out.</i>

04:35.011 --> 04:37.817
<i>DISPATCH OFFICER 1 :</i>

05:04.910 --> 05:06.571
Shit!

05:15.748 --> 05:16.614
Zwick, what you got?

05:16.649 --> 05:17.655
This one's dead.

05:20.995 --> 05:22.455
What the fuck, man?

05:22.490 --> 05:23.427
You shot him!

05:23.462 --> 05:24.897
Put your hands up
on your head!

05:24.933 --> 05:25.930
You piece of shit!

05:25.965 --> 05:27.632
Do it now!

05:32.105 --> 05:33.836
Come on, turn around.

05:35.909 --> 05:36.971
Let's go.

05:38.610 --> 05:41.112
Now, listen to me
very carefully, Miller.

05:41.147 --> 05:43.917
Your friend had a gun.

05:43.952 --> 05:46.018
He shot twice at me.

05:46.053 --> 05:48.647
And I defended myself.

05:48.682 --> 05:49.580
Do I have that right?

05:49.615 --> 05:50.349
Fuck you!

05:51.983 --> 05:54.686
Think of Beth and the baby.

05:58.029 --> 06:00.294
Okay.

06:00.329 --> 06:01.798
Let's go.

06:08.737 --> 06:10.642
PRISON OFFICER 1:
Open two!

07:53.147 --> 07:54.680
Welcome to the world.

07:59.311 --> 08:03.188
We gonna get you back
on your feet.

08:03.223 --> 08:05.290
I need a locksmith.

08:05.326 --> 08:08.160
Figured I could get you set up.

08:08.195 --> 08:10.458
Except I'm a felon.

08:10.494 --> 08:11.459
They took my cert.

08:11.494 --> 08:12.296
You know that.

08:12.331 --> 08:13.130
Oh, we'll put you down

08:13.166 --> 08:15.828
as handyman on the books
for your PO.

08:15.863 --> 08:17.102
Just until you get sorted.

08:17.138 --> 08:19.133
Whatever it takes.

08:21.105 --> 08:23.467
I just want to make things
right with Beth and Lindsay.

08:24.911 --> 08:27.680
Did you ever tell them what
really went down that night?

08:37.890 --> 08:41.661
FRANK:
Say hello
to your new accommodations.

08:43.962 --> 08:46.858
There's a shower next
to the shitter in the back.

08:46.893 --> 08:48.058
Man, you have no idea

08:48.093 --> 08:49.133
how happy I am to hear that.

08:52.934 --> 08:55.041
I think you two have met before.

08:55.076 --> 08:56.370
You kidding me?

08:56.405 --> 08:57.041
Yeah.

08:57.076 --> 08:58.207
What?

08:59.243 --> 09:01.171
I thought this thing would be
a bunch of spare parts by now.

09:01.206 --> 09:03.309
Man, I kept it running
for you.

09:03.344 --> 09:06.153
Kept it just the way
you like it, dents and all.

09:06.188 --> 09:08.017
Even added a few new ones.

09:09.223 --> 09:10.888
Thank you, Frank.

09:12.225 --> 09:14.056
Something else.

09:14.756 --> 09:16.756
This is my old phone.

09:16.791 --> 09:18.495
I got you a cheap plan.

09:18.531 --> 09:22.169
You pay the first every month.

09:22.204 --> 09:25.496
And uh, here's an advance.

09:32.213 --> 09:34.846
Lock up after you leave.

09:36.318 --> 09:39.976
Hey Frank, what's up with April?

09:40.012 --> 09:41.213
As far as I know,

09:41.248 --> 09:44.347
she stayed
in that foster care situation.

09:44.383 --> 09:46.620
I took my stab at being
mentor material

09:46.656 --> 09:48.360
to you and Kevin.

09:48.395 --> 09:51.256
You see how that worked out.

09:51.292 --> 09:55.360
Uh, after the trial,
I reached out to her.

09:55.396 --> 09:58.705
She didn't seem interested
in staying in touch.

10:00.469 --> 10:02.038
Alright.

10:02.937 --> 10:05.208
Don't burn down the place.

10:05.243 --> 10:06.937
I won't.

10:56.323 --> 10:57.161
<i>BETH :</i>
<i>This is Fisher.</i>

10:57.196 --> 10:58.431
Hi Beth.

10:58.466 --> 11:00.232
<i>BETH :</i>
<i>Miller?</i>

11:00.267 --> 11:03.135
I just got out.

11:03.171 --> 11:04.368
Can we meet?

11:04.404 --> 11:07.004
Can I see Lindsay?

11:30.163 --> 11:31.330
Hi.

11:31.365 --> 11:32.331
ROSIE:
Hi Lindsay.

11:32.366 --> 11:33.331
You're sticking to me.

11:34.234 --> 11:35.826
Say hello.

11:35.861 --> 11:37.500
Hi.

11:37.535 --> 11:38.303
Let's sit down.

11:38.338 --> 11:39.740
Yeah, thanks.

11:41.374 --> 11:42.407
Oh my gosh!

11:42.442 --> 11:43.935
Lindsay, you're so big.

11:45.339 --> 11:47.838
What are you in like,
fifth grade now?

11:47.873 --> 11:48.479
Sixth.

11:48.514 --> 11:50.311
MILLER:
Ah, sixth.

11:55.052 --> 11:57.313
Hey Linds,
why don't you go over to Rosie,

11:57.349 --> 11:59.685
and grab us a few slices of pie.

11:59.720 --> 12:00.293
Yeah?

12:00.328 --> 12:01.820
Any flavor you want.

12:01.855 --> 12:02.387
I'll pick.

12:02.422 --> 12:03.194
You pick, you choose.

12:03.229 --> 12:03.695
Okay.

12:12.934 --> 12:15.006
You look great, Beth.

12:18.211 --> 12:18.836
Miller.

12:18.871 --> 12:19.740
What?

12:19.775 --> 12:20.939
What is this?

12:20.975 --> 12:23.040
What do you mean?

12:23.075 --> 12:25.216
This is lunch.

12:25.251 --> 12:26.111
Right.

12:26.147 --> 12:28.047
Two slices of lemon meringue.

12:28.082 --> 12:29.790
And what does your dad like?

12:31.490 --> 12:33.420
I'm not sure.

12:37.965 --> 12:40.292
And what are we doing meeting
here of all places?

12:40.328 --> 12:42.569
Oh, we used to come here
all the time.

12:42.604 --> 12:44.697
So,
I just had good memories here.

12:44.732 --> 12:46.104
Right.

12:46.139 --> 12:49.401
Something about those nights
sitting up at that counter.

12:49.436 --> 12:50.707
Waiting for you to finish
your shift.

12:50.742 --> 12:52.109
And I remember coming back

12:52.144 --> 12:55.310
and having to work doubles
after you went inside.

13:00.584 --> 13:02.378
I'm sorry.

13:02.414 --> 13:07.556
Miller, I'm here for Lindsay.

13:07.592 --> 13:09.258
You know...

13:13.966 --> 13:18.328
I came to see if I can
let our daughter

13:18.364 --> 13:20.240
have a relationship with you.

13:20.275 --> 13:22.574
I'm her father.

13:22.609 --> 13:25.307
Not for the last 10 years.

13:30.510 --> 13:33.853
This is no excuse
but 10 years ago,

13:33.888 --> 13:37.984
I was afraid I couldn't provide
for you guys.

13:38.019 --> 13:39.483
And so I fucked up.

13:39.519 --> 13:44.029
I made a really, really
bad decision.

13:45.433 --> 13:48.200
A really bad decision.

13:48.235 --> 13:50.134
Jesus.

13:51.867 --> 13:54.666
Kevin died.

14:03.316 --> 14:03.910
Look.

14:05.853 --> 14:08.452
I want you to spend time
with her, okay?

14:08.488 --> 14:10.385
I really do.

14:11.324 --> 14:13.025
So, I...

14:13.061 --> 14:17.353
I need to know that you're not
gonna abandon her again.

14:17.388 --> 14:19.194
She can't handle that.

14:19.229 --> 14:22.034
What do I have to do
to prove it to you?

14:24.504 --> 14:26.698
Stick around.

14:34.648 --> 14:38.017
A lunch date isn't enough.

14:40.587 --> 14:42.521
You got to be patient.

14:42.556 --> 14:43.686
It's been 10 years.

14:43.722 --> 14:45.216
FRANK:
I get it.

14:45.251 --> 14:46.359
You've been in there.

14:46.394 --> 14:47.651
Nothing to do

14:47.687 --> 14:51.096
but think about who you have
on the outside.

14:51.131 --> 14:53.832
And then you get on the outside
and you realize that

14:53.867 --> 14:56.567
everybody else has been
moving on.

14:56.602 --> 14:58.031
Except for you.

14:58.066 --> 14:58.736
FRANK:
Except me?

14:58.771 --> 15:01.002
What do you mean except me?

15:01.038 --> 15:02.899
You see this empire I've built?

15:02.934 --> 15:05.503
No, I just mean that you
didn't turn your back on me.

15:05.538 --> 15:08.539
No, I'd never turn my back
on you.

15:08.575 --> 15:12.678
Beth moved on
and you fucked up bad.

15:13.454 --> 15:14.718
Thanks, Frank.

15:14.754 --> 15:16.279
FRANK:
I mean real bad.

15:16.314 --> 15:17.183
Yeah, I get it.

15:17.219 --> 15:19.789
She bounced back all by herself.

15:19.824 --> 15:21.852
She doesn't need you.

15:21.887 --> 15:26.698
But if you're patient,
if you keep your nose clean,

15:26.733 --> 15:27.998
if you're good to Lindsay,

15:28.033 --> 15:30.597
and if you take care
of yourself,

15:30.633 --> 15:33.796
someday she might remember
what you two used to have

15:33.831 --> 15:37.472
and want just a little bit
of that back.

15:40.472 --> 15:45.315
Man, when'd you get so deep?

15:45.350 --> 15:50.122
I'm just a man who made
a lot of mistakes in life.

15:55.422 --> 15:57.122
Rise and shine,
Good Behavior.

15:57.157 --> 15:58.462
You got a job.

15:58.497 --> 16:00.462
Okay.

16:01.302 --> 16:02.497
Okay.

16:19.785 --> 16:21.681
You're the locksmith?

16:22.547 --> 16:23.653
You called us, didn't you?

16:23.689 --> 16:25.652
That's cute.

16:26.654 --> 16:29.659
These digital locks,
they're the best, right?

16:29.695 --> 16:30.886
Definitely.

16:30.922 --> 16:33.497
And I can change the code
whenever I want?

16:33.532 --> 16:35.266
I guess.

16:35.301 --> 16:38.528
GARRETT:
You think you could do
a few more units?

16:38.564 --> 16:40.130
Yeah, I got more stock in here.

16:40.165 --> 16:40.804
Great.

16:40.839 --> 16:42.939
Let's get it going.

16:42.975 --> 16:44.741
So, all these rentals are yours?

16:44.776 --> 16:45.668
GARRETT:
Yeah.

16:45.704 --> 16:46.769
With tenants coming
and going,

16:46.805 --> 16:50.012
it'll be nice just to be able
to reset some codes.

16:50.047 --> 16:52.644
Looks like business is good.

16:52.679 --> 16:54.350
You know,
you came highly recommended.

16:54.385 --> 16:57.182
Well, there's not a lock
that Frank can't fix.

16:57.217 --> 16:58.348
No, not Frank.

16:58.383 --> 17:01.021
Miller, right?

17:01.056 --> 17:02.020
Miller Graham.

17:02.055 --> 17:03.354
Yeah.

17:03.389 --> 17:04.530
Someone referred you.

17:04.565 --> 17:05.465
I doubt it, man.

17:05.500 --> 17:06.497
I just started.

17:06.532 --> 17:07.758
No.

17:07.793 --> 17:08.799
April Reyes,
this girl that works for me,

17:08.834 --> 17:09.692
she said you were good

17:09.728 --> 17:11.528
and I thought,
"good locksmith?"

17:11.564 --> 17:12.396
What the fuck does that mean?

17:12.431 --> 17:13.636
April works for you?

17:13.671 --> 17:14.531
Mm-hmm.

17:14.567 --> 17:15.933
And she lives right over here.

17:17.042 --> 17:19.678
I give her a break on the rent.

17:19.713 --> 17:21.576
She a friend of yours?

17:22.647 --> 17:23.374
Yeah.

17:23.409 --> 17:24.479
I used to know her.

17:24.514 --> 17:27.652
Well, you must have left quite
an impression.

18:14.967 --> 18:17.770
I'm looking for a locksmith.

18:17.805 --> 18:19.772
Think you can help me out?

18:19.808 --> 18:21.664
No, sorry I'm just a handyman.

18:21.699 --> 18:23.734
But I'll see if Frank's in.

18:23.769 --> 18:26.542
What about that job
I just got you?

18:31.584 --> 18:32.883
April?

18:32.918 --> 18:35.081
You didn't recognize me.

18:35.117 --> 18:37.115
I just uh...

18:37.150 --> 18:39.052
Damn.

18:39.087 --> 18:39.790
You're...

18:39.826 --> 18:43.421
What... an adult?

18:43.456 --> 18:45.455
All grown up, yeah.

18:48.265 --> 18:49.903
Thanks for getting me that job.

18:49.938 --> 18:50.934
Kevin would have wanted
to see you

18:50.969 --> 18:52.832
get back on your feet.

18:57.805 --> 19:02.138
So, what are you up to
now that you're out?

19:03.674 --> 19:05.443
You're looking at it.

19:05.478 --> 19:06.947
No more safe cracking?

19:06.982 --> 19:08.713
No.

19:08.749 --> 19:11.591
That's a mistake
I won't make again.

19:11.626 --> 19:12.882
That's too bad.

19:12.917 --> 19:14.825
I heard you were pretty good
at it.

19:14.861 --> 19:16.628
Yeah, people talk.

19:16.664 --> 19:17.421
Oh, come on.

19:17.456 --> 19:18.764
You were good.

19:18.799 --> 19:19.730
You were really good.

19:19.766 --> 19:21.291
I was okay.

19:21.326 --> 19:22.697
Okay?

19:24.032 --> 19:24.837
Alright.

19:24.872 --> 19:26.602
I was pretty fucking great.

19:28.436 --> 19:29.638
Well, for jobs like that,

19:29.674 --> 19:33.510
it must be really hard
to find a good partner, right?

19:36.016 --> 19:39.142
Someone you can trust entirely.

19:42.883 --> 19:45.957
I wish I never brought him
there that night.

19:45.992 --> 19:48.118
I'm not talking about Kevin.

19:50.391 --> 19:51.992
I need money, Miller.

19:52.027 --> 19:53.790
Bad.

19:53.826 --> 19:54.865
Are you in some kind
of trouble

19:54.900 --> 19:56.192
or something?

19:57.603 --> 20:00.636
I'll tell you if you say
you'll help me get out of it.

20:06.871 --> 20:09.744
You know I'd do anything
for you.

20:16.887 --> 20:17.657
Hey!

20:17.692 --> 20:18.852
Hey, wait a sec.

20:18.887 --> 20:20.393
No, people always say
they'll do anything for you

20:20.428 --> 20:22.653
right before they tell you
why they won't do anything.

20:22.688 --> 20:24.327
April, the shit I was doing,

20:24.362 --> 20:25.823
it's the kind
of stuff people do,

20:25.858 --> 20:27.199
when they're trying
to cut corners.

20:27.234 --> 20:29.658
And I promise it catches up
with you.

20:29.694 --> 20:30.496
I did time for it.

20:30.531 --> 20:31.769
Yeah, you did time for it.

20:31.804 --> 20:32.905
And Kevin?

20:32.941 --> 20:34.566
What exactly are you asking me?

20:34.602 --> 20:35.802
Oh, I'm not asking you anything.

20:35.837 --> 20:38.910
You're not gonna help me,
so I'm not asking.

20:38.945 --> 20:40.878
Did that do it for Beth?

20:40.913 --> 20:42.810
"I did my time".

20:47.720 --> 20:48.381
Okay.

20:48.416 --> 20:50.314
Just wait a second.

20:50.349 --> 20:51.118
Hold on.

20:51.154 --> 20:52.688
Let's talk.

21:08.634 --> 21:11.235
Sounded good out there.

21:11.270 --> 21:14.279
I think April just asked me
to help her with a robbery.

21:14.314 --> 21:15.946
That's not someone your PO
would want you

21:15.982 --> 21:17.878
to associate with.

21:19.452 --> 21:21.787
Still, I got to find some way
to help her.

21:21.822 --> 21:23.714
Not like that.

21:23.749 --> 21:25.919
Keep your eyes on the prize.

21:28.092 --> 21:29.553
You're right.

21:51.943 --> 21:53.984
You gotta be fucking kidding me.

22:23.675 --> 22:24.917
Hi officers.

22:24.952 --> 22:26.676
Is there a problem?

22:53.541 --> 22:55.943
Early release, huh?

22:57.182 --> 22:58.946
For good behavior.

23:01.756 --> 23:03.049
Come out.

23:04.385 --> 23:05.716
Let's go!

23:05.751 --> 23:07.860
Step out of the vehicle.

23:17.763 --> 23:19.769
What do you want, Zwick?

23:22.734 --> 23:25.475
You know, I...

23:25.510 --> 23:27.144
I don't know what sorts
of thoughts

23:27.179 --> 23:28.078
go through a man's head

23:28.114 --> 23:29.380
when he's locked in a box
for 10 years.

23:29.416 --> 23:31.076
But I just thought I'd pay you
a visit.

23:31.112 --> 23:33.882
You know, bring you up
to speed on a few things.

23:35.615 --> 23:37.818
I'm retiring.

23:37.854 --> 23:39.984
I'm gonna spend my afternoons
playing golf

23:40.019 --> 23:42.427
and getting buzzed on
Bud Lights.

23:42.462 --> 23:44.929
And I have you to thank partly
for that.

23:44.965 --> 23:45.797
Busting you

23:45.832 --> 23:46.824
and your friend was one
of the things

23:46.860 --> 23:49.198
that got bumped to Lieutenant.

23:49.233 --> 23:52.128
But you know,

23:52.163 --> 23:56.003
these gentlemen
are not retiring.

23:56.777 --> 23:57.706
Miller,

23:57.741 --> 24:00.071
please meet Detectives Perez
and Jones.

24:00.106 --> 24:04.746
Detectives Perez and Jones,
meet Miller.

24:04.781 --> 24:06.611
Man, you told me to never
breathe a word.

24:06.646 --> 24:07.449
And I didn't.

24:07.484 --> 24:08.380
And I commend you for that.

24:08.415 --> 24:08.919
I do.

24:08.954 --> 24:09.448
I do.

24:09.483 --> 24:10.153
I just...

24:10.189 --> 24:11.120
Just hey, come on.

24:11.156 --> 24:12.448
Hey, hey...

24:14.327 --> 24:17.189
I need you to know something.

24:17.224 --> 24:20.831
That if you ever try
and fuck with me in any way,

24:20.866 --> 24:24.999
these gentlemen can and will
make your life miserable.

24:31.969 --> 24:32.735
What are you doing?

24:43.288 --> 24:45.151
We got something.

24:45.818 --> 24:48.286
Well, well, well Miller.

24:49.230 --> 24:50.924
He's a convicted felon, Chief.

24:50.960 --> 24:52.622
He had his locksmithing
certification revoked.

24:52.657 --> 24:53.830
Yeah,

24:53.865 --> 24:55.865
but did you actually see him
use the kit though?

24:57.136 --> 24:58.130
I mean, no sir,

24:58.165 --> 24:59.429
but you got to understand,
is this guy here--

24:59.465 --> 25:02.674
Then what the hell is he doing
in my station in cuffs?

25:05.146 --> 25:07.173
Are you out of your mind?

25:08.213 --> 25:09.805
It was Zwick.

25:09.841 --> 25:11.183
Oh, come on.

25:11.219 --> 25:12.481
Zwick wasn't anyone near this.

25:12.517 --> 25:14.053
I was making a run for Frank.

25:14.088 --> 25:15.847
It's a locksmith van.

25:15.883 --> 25:17.148
There's equipment in the back.

25:17.184 --> 25:19.417
Then, don't drive around
in a locksmith van.

25:19.452 --> 25:22.460
They would have pulled me over
if I was on roller blades.

25:22.496 --> 25:23.726
It didn't matter
what I was driving.

25:23.761 --> 25:25.690
Everything matters
at this point, Miller.

25:25.726 --> 25:27.122
You're on parole.

25:27.158 --> 25:29.828
Another mistake and you're done.

25:29.863 --> 25:31.661
Look, next time, detectives,

25:31.696 --> 25:35.575
just use a little due diligence
before you haul someone in here.

25:44.184 --> 25:44.817
Detective Fisher.

25:44.852 --> 25:46.619
Chief.

25:48.253 --> 25:50.555
Mr. Graham.

25:50.591 --> 25:53.817
You can't locksmith
without a certificate.

25:53.853 --> 25:55.017
I know that, sir.

25:55.052 --> 25:56.360
I'm just a handyman.

25:56.395 --> 25:57.527
Yeah, you mentioned that.

25:57.562 --> 26:00.166
But I don't know
if I believe it.

26:00.201 --> 26:01.290
But as there's no evidence

26:01.326 --> 26:03.200
of any illegal activity
on your part,

26:03.236 --> 26:04.493
you're free to go.

26:04.528 --> 26:07.233
But if I ever see you
in this station again,

26:07.269 --> 26:10.075
I will call your parole
officer, you understand that?

26:10.110 --> 26:11.809
I understand.

26:14.115 --> 26:15.673
You're free to go.

26:15.709 --> 26:17.276
Uncuff him.

26:25.983 --> 26:27.386
SHARON:
Okay.

26:27.421 --> 26:30.260
Let's start with having you
come by two times a week.

26:30.295 --> 26:31.255
Twice a week?

26:31.290 --> 26:33.296
Late to your first meeting,
Mr. Graham.

26:33.331 --> 26:34.530
Not a good look.

26:34.566 --> 26:35.901
That's not gonna happen again.

26:35.936 --> 26:37.303
Good.

26:37.338 --> 26:39.736
I'll see you next Monday
on time.

26:39.772 --> 26:42.141
Oh, and grab the cup
on that window outside

26:42.176 --> 26:43.901
with your name on it.

26:43.936 --> 26:45.242
Bathroom's to the left.

26:45.278 --> 26:46.243
When you're done,

26:46.279 --> 26:48.079
put your sample on the tray
with the others.

26:48.115 --> 26:49.473
Yes, ma'am.

26:51.175 --> 26:53.083
MILLER:
Frank, you here?

26:53.118 --> 26:54.984
Yeah.

26:59.853 --> 27:02.184
You missed a job.

27:02.219 --> 27:03.293
Guy said you stood him up.

27:03.328 --> 27:05.324
Yeah, I'm sorry.

27:05.359 --> 27:08.258
Some shit came up today
that was beyond my control.

27:08.294 --> 27:10.159
FRANK:
Look, I know you just got out.

27:10.195 --> 27:12.529
But you can't be missing jobs.

27:12.564 --> 27:15.235
They got something called
“Yelp” nowadays.

27:17.868 --> 27:19.910
Hey uh,

27:19.946 --> 27:22.312
you think you could take me on
as an actual handyman?

27:22.347 --> 27:24.279
Actual handyman.

27:24.314 --> 27:25.643
Huh.

27:25.678 --> 27:27.053
Okay.

27:27.088 --> 27:29.144
No bump in pay.

27:29.179 --> 27:30.582
There are some benefits.

27:30.617 --> 27:31.986
Yeah?

27:32.021 --> 27:35.918
You get your own special mop
and bucket.

27:40.300 --> 27:41.332
Okay, Indie, paw, paw.

27:41.368 --> 27:42.234
BETH:
Linds, come on!

27:42.269 --> 27:43.432
We're gonna be late.

27:43.468 --> 27:44.432
I'm almost ready.

27:44.468 --> 27:46.765
Shake, good.

27:46.800 --> 27:48.336
Yes, good job.

27:48.371 --> 27:48.998
Ready?

27:49.034 --> 27:50.941
This isn't ready.

27:50.976 --> 27:53.468
Is that what you're wearing
to the party tonight?

27:53.504 --> 27:55.478
I'm not going
to the party tonight.

27:55.513 --> 27:56.781
Allison can't come over,

27:56.817 --> 28:00.009
so I thought you
and I could make some popcorn

28:00.045 --> 28:02.321
and watch a movie.

28:02.356 --> 28:04.055
Why, what's wrong with this?

28:04.090 --> 28:04.585
Nothing.

28:04.620 --> 28:06.490
It looks fine.

28:06.525 --> 28:08.794
Why don't you just ask dad?

28:08.829 --> 28:10.823
I think your father needs just
a little more time

28:10.858 --> 28:12.731
getting settled in.

28:12.766 --> 28:15.427
If he's not busy,
I'm sure he can handle it.

28:15.462 --> 28:17.365
And you can go to the party
and have fun for once.

28:17.928 --> 28:18.633
Fun?

28:18.668 --> 28:20.338
Remind me what that is?

28:20.373 --> 28:21.030
I'll think about it.

28:21.066 --> 28:22.434
Come on, let's go.

28:24.872 --> 28:26.310
Guys, yeah, alright.

28:26.346 --> 28:28.008
Alright, alright.

28:28.044 --> 28:29.945
Lieutenant Zwick's work
with this force

28:29.980 --> 28:32.542
has been a deep service
to our community

28:32.577 --> 28:36.321
and I would like to personally
congratulate him

28:36.356 --> 28:38.356
on an incredible career.

28:38.391 --> 28:40.091
OFFICERS:
Yeah.

28:40.126 --> 28:41.519
Speech!

28:45.496 --> 28:47.500
Um, I'm just...

28:47.535 --> 28:49.401
I'm happy
to have left the streets

28:49.437 --> 28:51.894
of Dos Caminos a little safer.

28:51.929 --> 28:53.298
And uh,

28:53.334 --> 28:55.508
serving with some of the
Borderland's finest

28:55.543 --> 28:59.311
has been the honor
of my lifetime.

28:59.346 --> 29:02.246
And so uh, thank you.

29:02.281 --> 29:04.843
Um, and...

29:04.878 --> 29:05.950
One more thing.

29:07.513 --> 29:10.512
Miller Graham,
the man I put away the night

29:10.548 --> 29:12.581
I was under fire
in the line of duty

29:12.616 --> 29:15.760
has recently been released
from prison.

29:15.795 --> 29:19.392
So uh, watch your six out
there, fellas.

29:22.160 --> 29:23.594
Oh, and of course,

29:23.629 --> 29:27.371
attendance at my party later on
is mandatory, alright.

29:27.407 --> 29:28.808
Fisher, my office.

29:34.673 --> 29:40.182
Beth, with my retirement
we are down a man on Vice.

29:41.819 --> 29:45.189
I'd like you to fill that slot.

29:45.224 --> 29:45.751
Wow.

29:46.821 --> 29:48.392
Really, um....

29:48.428 --> 29:50.494
Here you go, boys.

29:50.529 --> 29:52.329
I'm just a little um...

29:52.364 --> 29:54.056
Surprised?

29:55.102 --> 29:55.367
Yes.

29:55.402 --> 29:57.392
Yeah.

29:57.427 --> 29:59.562
I'm not as stupid as I look.

29:59.597 --> 30:02.441
And I'm sure it hasn't always
been easy

30:02.476 --> 30:04.109
having me as a supervisor

30:04.144 --> 30:07.503
given what happened between me
and that asshole ex of yours.

30:07.539 --> 30:09.507
Just consider this my way
of saying,

30:09.543 --> 30:12.049
I always thought you were
good police, Fisher.

30:15.113 --> 30:16.083
Oh well, I--

30:16.118 --> 30:19.122
I can't just drop
my other cases.

30:20.493 --> 30:21.485
Yeah, by the way,

30:21.520 --> 30:23.825
I wouldn't worry too much
about that.

30:23.861 --> 30:26.495
Those will all get transitioned.

30:26.530 --> 30:27.590
This is--

30:27.626 --> 30:29.693
this is the real police work
here, you know.

30:31.831 --> 30:35.974
Beth, these men can't drink
their whisky until you accept.

30:43.515 --> 30:44.039
Then I accept.

30:44.074 --> 30:44.810
Whoo!

30:44.846 --> 30:45.812
There it is.

30:49.653 --> 30:50.353
Ah, there it is.

30:50.388 --> 30:51.049
Alright.

30:51.084 --> 30:52.114
Out of here, all of you.

30:52.149 --> 30:52.986
Thank you.

30:53.022 --> 30:53.621
We'll see you out there, Fisher.

30:53.656 --> 30:54.652
Yes, yes.

31:00.566 --> 31:02.528
Oh, Lieutenant, um...

31:02.564 --> 31:04.961
What is it exactly that you'd
like me to jump into?

31:04.996 --> 31:06.229
Oh.

31:06.264 --> 31:07.332
Yeah, just you know,

31:07.367 --> 31:08.300
just really dig
into the case files.

31:08.335 --> 31:10.206
Get a sense of what we're
working on here.

31:12.212 --> 31:13.411
Sir.

31:35.301 --> 31:36.694
Alright.

31:39.470 --> 31:40.572
Hello?

31:40.607 --> 31:41.765
<i>BETH :</i>
<i>Hey.</i>

31:41.801 --> 31:45.403
Um, there's this thing tonight
at the King of Spades.

31:45.438 --> 31:46.611
<i>MILLER :</i>
<i>The cop bar?</i>

31:46.646 --> 31:47.879
<i>BETH :</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

31:47.915 --> 31:49.679
I was wondering if you could
pick Lindsay up

31:49.714 --> 31:50.882
from her piano lesson

31:50.917 --> 31:52.941
and spend a little bit
of time with her.

31:52.976 --> 31:55.487
I usually ask the neighbor,
but she's not around.

31:55.522 --> 31:56.379
No, I would love that.

31:56.414 --> 31:57.515
<i>BETH :</i>
<i>Great.</i>

31:57.550 --> 31:59.557
Okay, so,
you got to go over her homework,

31:59.592 --> 32:00.450
make sure she's done it.

32:00.486 --> 32:01.818
<i>MILLER :</i>
<i>Hold on.</i>

32:04.264 --> 32:05.924
Okay.

32:05.959 --> 32:06.862
Homework.

32:06.898 --> 32:10.028
And no fast food, real dinner.

32:10.063 --> 32:12.070
No fast food.

32:12.670 --> 32:14.229
Okay, what else?

32:14.264 --> 32:15.174
That's it.

32:15.209 --> 32:16.701
Oh.

32:17.768 --> 32:19.609
I can drop her off at your
house after...

32:19.644 --> 32:20.236
Uh no, no, no.

32:20.271 --> 32:21.039
The bar is fine.

32:21.074 --> 32:22.511
Uh, I gotta go.

32:22.546 --> 32:23.073
Okay.

32:23.109 --> 32:24.546
Beth, um...

32:24.581 --> 32:26.043
Yeah?

32:26.078 --> 32:28.253
Thank you.

32:28.288 --> 32:29.813
You bet.

32:55.882 --> 32:57.407
MISS DANDUS:
See you next week, okay.

32:57.443 --> 32:58.240
LINDSAY:
Bye, Miss Dandus.

32:58.275 --> 32:59.810
Thank you.

33:02.388 --> 33:02.947
Hi, dad.

33:02.982 --> 33:04.688
Hey.

33:04.723 --> 33:06.489
That sounded so good.

33:06.524 --> 33:07.625
Thanks.

33:07.660 --> 33:08.920
Got all your stuff?

33:08.955 --> 33:09.693
Yeah.

33:09.728 --> 33:10.955
Alright, let's bounce.

33:10.990 --> 33:12.262
Okay.

33:14.627 --> 33:16.431
Do you anything you're really
good at?

33:17.832 --> 33:19.698
Hm.

33:21.002 --> 33:22.564
Not really.

33:22.599 --> 33:24.775
What about picking locks?

33:24.810 --> 33:27.479
Mom told me you're the best.

33:27.515 --> 33:29.105
She did, did she?

33:29.140 --> 33:29.972
Mhmmm.

33:33.752 --> 33:35.120
Will you show me?

33:39.087 --> 33:40.019
I see that smile.

33:42.956 --> 33:43.961
Alright.

33:43.997 --> 33:45.658
Give me a couple
of your bobby pins.

33:49.094 --> 33:50.458
Okay.

33:50.494 --> 33:51.529
Most people think

33:51.564 --> 33:53.566
picking locks
is like mysterious.

33:53.602 --> 33:56.568
But locks are actually kind
of easy to crack.

33:56.603 --> 33:58.239
You don't even need a kit
like I use.

33:58.275 --> 34:01.745
Alright,
so this is your tension lever.

34:01.780 --> 34:04.774
And this is your pick.

34:04.809 --> 34:06.182
So, we're going
to take the tension lever

34:06.217 --> 34:08.811
and stick it in the bottom
of the lock.

34:08.847 --> 34:10.689
Okay, now there's five pins
in this lock.

34:10.724 --> 34:12.685
We're gonna take the pick

34:12.720 --> 34:16.851
and put it in the lock
just above the tension lever.

34:16.887 --> 34:20.231
And we're going to feel
for the pins.

34:20.266 --> 34:22.391
Now, one of the pins is
gonna be harder to push up

34:22.426 --> 34:23.735
than the others.

34:23.771 --> 34:25.794
It's called the "seized pin".

34:25.830 --> 34:28.538
And that's the one
we're looking for.

34:28.573 --> 34:30.574
So...

34:30.610 --> 34:31.567
Okay there.

34:31.603 --> 34:33.002
There, there, there, that guy.

34:33.038 --> 34:37.149
Right now push him up
while you turn the tension lever

34:39.784 --> 34:41.978
and guess what?

34:47.218 --> 34:48.052
Hey.

34:48.087 --> 34:49.392
Hey.

34:50.721 --> 34:53.222
Oh, looks like someone had fun.

34:53.257 --> 34:54.292
Yeah.

34:54.327 --> 34:55.499
We had a good time.

34:55.534 --> 34:56.729
We did.

34:58.171 --> 35:01.263
Homework is done
and we had a nice dinner.

35:01.298 --> 35:02.800
Great.

35:02.835 --> 35:05.236
And you are my excuse
for a quick exit, so...

35:05.944 --> 35:06.642
Let's get you home, missy.

35:06.677 --> 35:07.404
Okay.

35:07.439 --> 35:08.746
That's a lot of people.

35:08.781 --> 35:10.548
What's the occasion?

35:10.583 --> 35:11.339
Hey, baby?

35:11.374 --> 35:12.212
Yeah?

35:12.248 --> 35:13.550
Why don't you wait in the car?

35:13.585 --> 35:14.311
Sure.

35:14.346 --> 35:15.385
BETH:
Okay.

35:17.017 --> 35:20.252
Um...

35:20.287 --> 35:22.889
Zwick's retirement.

35:22.924 --> 35:24.563
Mm.

35:24.598 --> 35:27.455
Miller, come on.

35:27.491 --> 35:28.733
I had to go.

35:28.768 --> 35:31.632
Yeah, it's your job.

35:31.668 --> 35:37.940
Well, with Zwick out,
there's an opening on Vice, so.

35:37.975 --> 35:40.841
And you're taking it?

35:40.876 --> 35:42.847
Yeah.

35:42.883 --> 35:45.307
Anyway, thank you for tonight.

35:45.342 --> 35:47.076
Yeah.

35:48.686 --> 35:50.312
Night.

35:50.347 --> 35:52.257
Night.

35:58.828 --> 36:00.823
Miller!

36:00.858 --> 36:04.936
Did uh,
Beth tell you the good news?

36:04.972 --> 36:07.170
That you no longer have
a badge?

36:07.205 --> 36:08.771
Yeah, I'm going home
to celebrate.

36:10.374 --> 36:13.168
That's--
That's actually pretty funny.

36:14.345 --> 36:20.018
You know uh,
Vice is a dangerous unit.

36:20.054 --> 36:23.946
I mean things happen out there,
okay.

36:23.981 --> 36:25.482
And all you got
are your fellow detectives

36:25.517 --> 36:27.325
to watch your back.

36:29.922 --> 36:32.990
It's a good thing she's got
Perez and Jones.

36:48.611 --> 36:51.112
April, what the hell are you
doing here?

36:51.147 --> 36:53.510
I'm in trouble, Miller.

36:53.545 --> 36:55.478
The man I work for...

36:55.513 --> 36:57.381
Real estate guy?

36:57.416 --> 36:58.950
That's a front.

37:00.552 --> 37:02.360
A front for what?

37:09.934 --> 37:12.161
He runs girls.

37:14.940 --> 37:17.235
So, you're like a...

37:17.271 --> 37:18.772
A call girl.

37:21.873 --> 37:26.411
Don't you dare fucking
judge me.

37:26.446 --> 37:28.813
I didn't choose this.

37:28.848 --> 37:32.156
After Kevin died,
I didn't have anyone.

37:32.191 --> 37:34.892
There was no one there
to stop it.

37:34.927 --> 37:37.692
He won't let me go.

37:37.727 --> 37:40.957
Last year, I tried to run
and he beat me so bad

37:40.992 --> 37:43.935
I was in the hospital
for three weeks.

37:43.970 --> 37:46.364
And he's still hurting me.

38:02.748 --> 38:04.053
We have to go to the police now.

38:04.088 --> 38:05.921
No, they're in on it.

38:05.957 --> 38:06.883
Beth's not.

38:06.919 --> 38:09.554
I'm telling you
it is not gonna work.

38:09.589 --> 38:11.087
I need to get out of town.

38:11.122 --> 38:12.854
I need to go somewhere
they will never find me.

38:12.889 --> 38:14.029
And I need money to do it.

38:14.065 --> 38:16.467
You know I can't.

38:16.502 --> 38:17.934
So, you're just gonna
let them keep hurting me?

38:17.970 --> 38:18.928
I swore to myself

38:18.963 --> 38:20.597
when I walked through
those gates

38:20.632 --> 38:21.397
that I'd stay clean

38:21.433 --> 38:23.065
and I'd spend the rest
of my life

38:23.100 --> 38:24.468
making it up to you, Beth,
and Lindsay.

38:24.503 --> 38:25.539
APRIL:
Yeah.

38:25.574 --> 38:27.746
Just not necessarily
in that order.

38:27.781 --> 38:28.939
Hey, that's...

38:28.974 --> 38:30.940
Look, you don't give a shit
about me.

38:30.976 --> 38:32.909
You say you want to make it up
to me,

38:32.944 --> 38:34.309
but just tell me
the fucking truth.

38:34.344 --> 38:36.052
You just care about getting
your real family back.

38:36.087 --> 38:36.951
You're family, too.

38:36.986 --> 38:37.681
No.

38:37.716 --> 38:40.983
Kevin was my real family.

38:41.018 --> 38:43.260
He was the only family
I ever had.

38:43.296 --> 38:44.896
And none of this
would have happened

38:44.931 --> 38:46.365
if he was still alive.

38:51.035 --> 38:53.603
What's the job?

38:55.974 --> 38:58.303
A poker game.

38:58.339 --> 38:59.843
Easy money.

38:59.879 --> 39:01.846
You hit it.

39:01.881 --> 39:04.639
I take the cash.

39:04.674 --> 39:05.648
And I run.

39:06.979 --> 39:09.212
APRIL:
Then you'll have made it up
to me.

39:10.983 --> 39:12.923
It'll just be
a few questions, ma'am.

39:26.169 --> 39:27.696
BETH:
Hm.

39:27.731 --> 39:29.705
I know this one.

39:29.740 --> 39:31.634
Used to run around
with my friend's younger sister.

39:31.669 --> 39:32.667
PEREZ:
Yeah?

39:32.703 --> 39:33.977
Small town.

39:47.557 --> 39:49.719
Zero record
of prostitution arrests

39:49.754 --> 39:51.988
in the last three years.

39:52.023 --> 39:54.156
Like I said,
Fisher, small town.

39:54.192 --> 39:56.666
What, people don't pay
for sex in small towns.

39:59.837 --> 40:02.104
MILLER:
Yo, I thought you said
this was a poker game.

40:02.139 --> 40:03.442
APRIL:
It is.

40:04.443 --> 40:07.044
Looks like a whole fucking
party to me.

40:07.079 --> 40:08.739
That's a lot of eyes.

40:08.775 --> 40:11.742
It's nothing you can't handle.

40:11.778 --> 40:13.050
Garrett does this every month.

40:13.085 --> 40:14.076
He dresses up the game

40:14.111 --> 40:17.379
like it's some
classy casino night.

40:17.414 --> 40:19.984
Charges a high buy-in,
the buy-in goes into the pot.

40:20.019 --> 40:21.322
And then he takes a big cut
for hosting,

40:21.357 --> 40:22.559
on top of what he makes

40:22.594 --> 40:24.193
from the girls working
the players all night.

40:24.228 --> 40:25.389
And who are the players?

40:25.424 --> 40:27.159
Execs.

40:27.194 --> 40:29.056
Business types that drive
into town just for the game.

40:29.092 --> 40:31.032
They're definitely not trouble.

40:32.698 --> 40:34.371
So, you take the money,

40:34.406 --> 40:35.898
and I'll meet you back
at Frank's

40:35.933 --> 40:37.040
when I'm done for the night.

40:37.075 --> 40:39.340
What's the take?

40:39.375 --> 40:40.604
Half a million dollars.

40:40.639 --> 40:41.609
MILLER:
What?

40:41.645 --> 40:43.112
That's a fucking shit ton
of money.

40:43.147 --> 40:44.139
APRIL:
Yeah.

40:44.174 --> 40:45.484
Enough for me
to start a new life.

40:48.078 --> 40:50.912
MILLER:
So, what about security?

40:50.947 --> 40:52.315
You're looking at it.

40:57.393 --> 40:59.025
Why am I not surprised?

41:00.164 --> 41:01.423
Three years ago,

41:01.459 --> 41:03.595
all these women were picked up
on prostitution charges.

41:03.630 --> 41:05.803
Then arrests dry up.

41:05.838 --> 41:06.598
Okay.

41:06.633 --> 41:07.635
So, we booked them,

41:07.670 --> 41:08.600
