We should have some privacy.

42:38.197 --> 42:39.028
MAN 1:
Like that.

42:39.063 --> 42:39.722
Yeah.

43:24.075 --> 43:25.039
Shit!

43:27.276 --> 43:28.170
Fuck.

43:28.205 --> 43:29.411
I'm so sorry.
Let me see that.

43:29.446 --> 43:30.913
Um, let me help you.

43:32.878 --> 43:34.185
I'll help you carry it.

43:35.815 --> 43:37.411
It was an accident.

43:37.447 --> 43:38.387
GARRETT:
Do you know how embarrassing--

43:38.422 --> 43:39.418
Get over here and sit.

43:39.453 --> 43:40.223
Ow!

43:40.259 --> 43:41.357
You're hurting me.

43:42.427 --> 43:45.128
MAN 2:

43:45.163 --> 43:45.756
Thank you.

44:36.807 --> 44:37.848
Come on!

44:46.289 --> 44:46.982
Let go!

44:52.196 --> 44:53.556
Hey.

44:56.493 --> 44:58.768
You better know how
to use that thing.

44:58.803 --> 45:01.300
You're gonna need it
to get out of here.

45:03.243 --> 45:04.275
What are you doing?

45:04.310 --> 45:05.843
You-- you got the money!

45:07.246 --> 45:08.676
Don't be stupid.

45:08.712 --> 45:10.380
There are 30 people out there.

45:10.415 --> 45:11.348
You pull that trigger,

45:11.383 --> 45:13.213
you'll be dead before
you reach the door.

45:21.227 --> 45:23.227
Who are you?

45:39.268 --> 45:40.242
Hey, stop right there!

45:40.277 --> 45:41.109
Freeze!

45:52.083 --> 45:53.521
Hey, stay calm, man.

45:53.556 --> 45:54.025
MILLER:
You!

45:54.060 --> 45:54.889
Back off

45:54.924 --> 45:56.050
or I'll blow
her fucking brains out.

45:56.085 --> 45:56.922
Let me go!

45:56.958 --> 45:57.756
You don't wanna do this, man.

45:57.791 --> 45:59.094
I said back off!

46:01.357 --> 46:02.225
JONES:
Be the smart guy.

46:02.261 --> 46:03.560
We can all walk away
from this.

46:05.269 --> 46:06.101
Come on.

46:07.130 --> 46:08.030
Hey, hey, hey!

46:19.778 --> 46:21.446
Fuck!

46:23.213 --> 46:24.680
Enjoying your cocktail?

46:26.158 --> 46:27.381
Useless!

46:27.416 --> 46:28.457
And where the hell were you?

46:28.493 --> 46:30.017
He overpowered me.

46:30.052 --> 46:31.926
Really?

46:31.962 --> 46:33.396
You got something
to say about that?

46:33.431 --> 46:34.798
Just save it.

46:34.834 --> 46:37.297
Just find out who he is
and get my money back.

46:41.438 --> 46:42.874
Fucking...

47:08.527 --> 47:09.598
<i>APRIL :</i>
<i>Hey, it's April.</i>

47:09.633 --> 47:11.166
<i>Leave me a message.</i>

47:16.508 --> 47:17.031
<i>Hey, it's April.</i>

47:17.066 --> 47:18.001
Shit!

47:51.573 --> 47:53.542
April?

48:05.950 --> 48:07.886
April?

48:22.140 --> 48:25.267
Please tell me your father
didn't teach you that?

48:25.302 --> 48:27.036
I saw it on YouTube.

48:27.072 --> 48:28.236
Yeah, right!

48:28.271 --> 48:29.274
Hand 'em over

48:29.309 --> 48:30.613
before I throw you
in the slammer!

48:30.648 --> 48:32.139
Oh no, not the slammer.

48:34.586 --> 48:35.712
Eat your breakfast.

48:37.652 --> 48:38.550
Okay.

48:40.688 --> 48:41.522
Tanya?

48:41.557 --> 48:42.524
Beth.

48:42.559 --> 48:43.458
Long time.

48:43.493 --> 48:44.394
Yeah.

48:44.429 --> 48:45.462
Uh, Linds,

48:45.497 --> 48:46.331
why didn't you finish
getting ready for school?

48:46.366 --> 48:46.925
Uh, take Indie.

48:46.960 --> 48:47.793
Come on, Indie.

48:47.828 --> 48:48.255
Thank you.

48:48.291 --> 48:49.594
Come on in.

48:50.568 --> 48:51.400
There you go.

48:51.435 --> 48:53.563
Thanks.

48:53.598 --> 48:58.399
Um, so April and I,
we work together,

48:58.434 --> 49:01.269
you know like um...

49:01.304 --> 49:02.571
entertaining.

49:02.606 --> 49:04.648
TANYA:
At first, I really liked it.

49:04.683 --> 49:06.383
You know, I had nice things.

49:06.419 --> 49:08.216
A home, car.

49:08.251 --> 49:10.112
So, when Garrett asked me
to April about it,

49:10.148 --> 49:11.352
I just did.

49:11.387 --> 49:14.082
You mean, Garrett Field,
the real estate developer?

49:14.117 --> 49:15.950
Yeah.

49:15.985 --> 49:18.392
And I mean I wouldn't have
asked April about it,

49:18.427 --> 49:20.963
if I knew that it was gonna
turn into what it did.

49:20.998 --> 49:24.600
You know, the car
and the clothes;

49:24.636 --> 49:25.467
none of its ours.

49:28.039 --> 49:30.498
He even puts us up
in these nice places,

49:30.534 --> 49:32.568
but he owns them all, you know.

49:32.603 --> 49:35.138
If any of us ever try
to get out,

49:35.173 --> 49:36.781
it would be bad.

49:36.816 --> 49:39.942
Here, I want to show you
something.

49:39.978 --> 49:42.680
I don't know what'll happen
if he finds out I took these.

49:50.525 --> 49:53.229
April's been having a lot
of issues with Garrett.

49:53.265 --> 49:55.633
The other day she shows me
these bruises on her arm.

49:55.668 --> 49:56.667
And then last night I hear

49:56.702 --> 49:58.734
what sounds like a break-in
at her apartment.

49:58.769 --> 50:00.832
And now, she's just...

50:00.867 --> 50:02.402
gone.

50:02.437 --> 50:05.366
This morning I see Miller going
into her place.

50:05.401 --> 50:07.302
BETH:
Miller?

50:07.337 --> 50:09.171
Are you sure?

50:09.207 --> 50:11.049
It was him.

50:15.585 --> 50:17.550
Shit.

50:23.061 --> 50:26.658
This is a job April asked you
to pull.

50:31.834 --> 50:33.830
Are you insane?

50:34.540 --> 50:35.698
I can explain...

50:35.733 --> 50:38.202
No, that's a serious question
I'm asking

50:38.237 --> 50:39.776
and I need an answer.

50:39.811 --> 50:41.710
Are you out of your mind?

50:41.745 --> 50:42.744
They took her.

50:42.779 --> 50:44.139
She's missing.

50:44.174 --> 50:45.306
Oh.

50:45.341 --> 50:46.684
Oh, I'm--

50:46.719 --> 50:49.814
I'm trying to understand,

50:49.849 --> 50:55.222
why you would get yourself
involved in something like this?

50:55.257 --> 50:57.728
Do you want to go back
to prison?

50:57.763 --> 50:59.829
They're hurting her, Frank.

50:59.864 --> 51:02.032
She showed me the bruises.

51:02.067 --> 51:03.925
Okay, this girls needs
to get out of town

51:03.960 --> 51:05.668
and this was the only way
she could think of

51:05.704 --> 51:06.604
to get the money.

51:06.639 --> 51:08.666
The part I'm missing is,

51:08.702 --> 51:12.841
you explaining how
that's your responsibility.

51:12.876 --> 51:15.475
'Cause I owe her.

51:15.510 --> 51:17.775
What am I supposed to do
just let her get killed?

51:21.450 --> 51:26.256
Look, I know you have
a tough choice to make.

51:28.123 --> 51:30.584
But you made the wrong one.

51:30.619 --> 51:32.256
You gotta go to Beth.

51:32.291 --> 51:34.258
She's the one you owe.

51:34.293 --> 51:35.766
Take this cash back.

51:35.801 --> 51:37.701
Tell her to go find April.

51:37.736 --> 51:38.801
And let her do her job.

51:38.836 --> 51:40.703
It's not that simple.

51:40.739 --> 51:41.664
Zwick's involved.

51:41.699 --> 51:42.765
Well, that's even more
of a reason

51:42.801 --> 51:44.840
why you need to tell her
to watch your back.

51:44.875 --> 51:46.878
It's too dangerous.

51:46.913 --> 51:48.878
Trust me,
she's safer not knowing.

51:48.914 --> 51:50.211
I gotta handle this on my own.

51:50.246 --> 51:52.749
You better hope
that you find her

51:52.784 --> 51:55.645
before they find you.

51:55.680 --> 51:57.655
Just gonna go back
to Garrett's.

51:57.690 --> 51:59.488
She's there, I know it.

51:59.523 --> 52:02.919
Can I please just keep this
in the safe for one night?

52:06.898 --> 52:07.695
I want it out by morning.

52:07.730 --> 52:09.790
Okay.

52:09.826 --> 52:12.130
After this I'm done,
I promise.

52:31.720 --> 52:33.447
<i>GARRETT :</i>
<i>What the hell happened here?</i>

52:33.483 --> 52:34.916
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>I caught this one</i>
<i>with half her take</i>

52:34.951 --> 52:36.151
<i>stuffed in the bottom</i>
<i>of her purse.</i>

52:36.186 --> 52:37.925
<i>GARRETT :</i>
<i>So, you beat her half to death?</i>

52:37.961 --> 52:39.929
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>You want me</i>
<i>to protect your money or not?</i>

52:39.965 --> 52:42.199
<i>GARRETT :</i>
<i>Just not the face, Zwick.</i>
<i>Why do you keep doing this?</i>

52:42.234 --> 52:44.131
<i>She's worthless to me</i>
<i>for what, a month?</i>

52:44.167 --> 52:45.932
<i>That is coming out of your end.</i>

52:45.967 --> 52:47.371
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>Bullshit it's coming out</i>
<i>of my end--</i>

52:47.406 --> 52:48.470
<i>GARRETT :</i>
<i>I don't have time for this.</i>

52:48.505 --> 52:50.103
<i>Just take the girls back</i>
<i>to the development.</i>

52:50.138 --> 52:52.172
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>Perez and Jones will make sure</i>
<i>they get back alright.</i>

52:52.208 --> 52:54.108
<i>You and I, we're having a talk.</i>

52:54.143 --> 52:56.871
TANYA:
Garrett is nasty.

52:56.907 --> 52:59.014
But uh,
when he wants something done,

52:59.050 --> 53:00.776
it's usually one of those three.

53:00.811 --> 53:03.985
So, I couldn't go
to anyone else.

53:04.020 --> 53:07.049
Beth, can you help her?

53:08.892 --> 53:11.053
I'm gonna try.

53:19.804 --> 53:21.164
Hey Miller?

53:21.199 --> 53:22.871
Yo.

53:22.906 --> 53:24.367
You got a sec?

53:24.402 --> 53:25.639
Yeah, of course.

53:27.912 --> 53:29.339
Can I get you something?

53:29.374 --> 53:30.714
Beer, or water?

53:30.749 --> 53:31.715
Uh, I'm on duty.

53:31.750 --> 53:33.383
Thanks though.

53:35.014 --> 53:38.355
Hey, have you seen April at all
since you were released?

53:39.987 --> 53:40.821
No.

53:40.856 --> 53:42.716
No?

53:42.751 --> 53:44.018
Why is something wrong?

53:44.053 --> 53:47.564
Well, Tanya,
you remember Tanya, right?

53:47.599 --> 53:48.323
Yeah.

53:48.358 --> 53:49.331
Yeah.

53:49.366 --> 53:51.233
She lives across the street
from April.

53:51.269 --> 53:53.093
Thinks she saw something
the other night.

53:53.129 --> 53:56.540
So, I stopped by April's,
no one answered.

53:56.575 --> 53:57.871
So...

53:57.906 --> 53:59.876
Hm.

53:59.911 --> 54:02.236
I'm sure she's fine.

54:08.419 --> 54:09.780
You want to tell me
what really went down

54:09.815 --> 54:12.323
the day Perez
and Jones pulled you over?

54:14.090 --> 54:16.287
Exactly what you think.

54:16.322 --> 54:17.825
I was an idiot.

54:17.860 --> 54:22.029
I was driving around with a van
that says locksmith on the side.

54:22.064 --> 54:24.093
Miller, I know.

54:25.463 --> 54:26.903
You know what?

54:26.938 --> 54:29.604
I know they're dirty.

54:40.780 --> 54:44.081
The reason I fell in love
with you,

54:44.117 --> 54:47.490
it's because you do anything
for the people you care about.

54:48.392 --> 54:51.087
That's also the reason
I let you go.

54:53.432 --> 54:56.367
'Cause I know the way
your mind works, Miller.

54:57.893 --> 54:59.369
And I came here to tell you,

54:59.405 --> 55:01.939
that if you know anything
about what's going on,

55:01.974 --> 55:03.737
you gotta stay out of it.

55:05.072 --> 55:06.267
Okay.

55:06.302 --> 55:09.111
But I really don't know
what you're talking about.

55:09.146 --> 55:11.613
You gotta stay out of it.

55:12.816 --> 55:14.781
Promise.

55:15.621 --> 55:17.047
Okay.

55:20.416 --> 55:23.420
Oh uh, you taught Lindsay
how to pick my handcuffs?

55:23.456 --> 55:26.921
Uh, not directly.

55:26.956 --> 55:28.997
'Cause she's really good at it.

55:32.502 --> 55:35.065
Well, you've done a hell
of a job with her.

55:36.709 --> 55:37.933
You know,

55:37.968 --> 55:39.537
it's been nice seeing the two
of you

55:39.572 --> 55:40.778
spend some time together.

55:40.813 --> 55:42.479
She missed you.

55:50.713 --> 55:51.787
I'll see you.

55:51.822 --> 55:53.347
See ya.

56:26.717 --> 56:28.888
What's in the envelope?

56:28.924 --> 56:32.089
Just some narcotics stats
Stern wanted me to chase.

56:34.029 --> 56:35.492
Fisher?

56:54.111 --> 56:56.947
With this
and Tanya Saunders' testimony,

56:56.982 --> 56:58.781
we have enough to implicate
all of them.

56:58.817 --> 57:01.692
Tanya Saunders is a prostitute.

57:02.556 --> 57:03.455
Sir, with all due respect--

57:03.491 --> 57:07.056
Now you and I are gonna
investigate this.

57:07.092 --> 57:08.696
I'm gonna need to bring this
to State Police.

57:08.731 --> 57:11.392
I wanna be well-armed
for that conversation.

57:13.972 --> 57:15.163
In the meantime,

57:15.198 --> 57:18.968
we got a potential
missing person's case.

57:19.004 --> 57:21.571
Uh, can you find me
another witness,

57:21.606 --> 57:23.003
besides Tanya?

57:23.038 --> 57:24.072
I mean is there anyone else

57:24.108 --> 57:25.549
that might know something
about this

57:25.584 --> 57:29.143
that you can talk to
without kicking up any dust?

57:29.178 --> 57:31.755
Let me give it some thought,
sir.

57:31.790 --> 57:33.491
Okay.

57:38.457 --> 57:39.290
Uh, Beth?

57:39.325 --> 57:40.086
Yeah?

57:40.122 --> 57:42.225
Thanks for bringing this to me.

57:42.261 --> 57:44.266
We have a lot of cops
on the other side of that door

57:44.302 --> 57:45.632
who will not feel the same way.

57:45.668 --> 57:48.000
You understand what I'm trying
to say?

58:47.623 --> 58:54.572
Well, the cat burglar returns
to the scene of the crime.

58:55.737 --> 58:59.676
You're not big on doorbells,
huh?

58:59.711 --> 59:03.545
You've got some meaty balls
for a coward in a mask.

59:03.580 --> 59:06.175
Why don't you take
that thing off

59:06.210 --> 59:07.475
and tell me
where my fucking money is?

59:07.510 --> 59:09.917
If you let her go,
I'll make sure you get it back.

59:13.221 --> 59:13.980
Drink?

59:14.016 --> 59:16.025
I said let her go.

59:16.061 --> 59:17.959
I heard you.

59:17.994 --> 59:21.130
I just have no fucking idea
what you're talking about.

59:21.166 --> 59:23.032
Where's my money?

59:23.068 --> 59:24.034
April Reyes.

59:24.070 --> 59:25.135
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

59:25.170 --> 59:28.067
Easy, we're talking.

59:29.240 --> 59:31.070
Help me understand.

59:31.105 --> 59:33.410
Obviously, you've realized
you're over your head.

59:33.445 --> 59:35.371
And you want to give me
my money back.

59:37.380 --> 59:38.907
Where does April fit in?

59:38.942 --> 59:40.377
I know you have her.

59:40.413 --> 59:43.984
I came here to make a trade,
but I'm running out of patience.

59:45.154 --> 59:46.750
Alright.

59:46.785 --> 59:49.217
Money for April Reyes?

59:49.253 --> 59:51.788
The girl you used
as a human shield?

59:51.823 --> 59:53.260
I can make that deal.

1:00:30.368 --> 1:00:31.793
I don't-- I don't have her!

1:00:38.704 --> 1:00:39.504
Where is she?

1:00:39.539 --> 1:00:40.375
Please...

1:00:40.410 --> 1:00:43.142
I don't-- I don't know.

1:00:49.685 --> 1:00:51.981
Stop it.
I was fucking lying.

1:00:52.016 --> 1:00:53.387
I was-- I was just stalling.

1:00:53.423 --> 1:00:54.322
I don't have her.

1:00:54.357 --> 1:00:56.984
Then who does?

1:00:57.019 --> 1:00:58.260
I don't know.

1:01:09.865 --> 1:01:11.436
Zwick!

1:01:11.471 --> 1:01:12.371
Zwick!

1:01:15.306 --> 1:01:17.438
I told him to get
to the bottom of this.

1:01:17.474 --> 1:01:20.982
If she's a part of it,
he probably has her.

1:01:45.243 --> 1:01:46.968
That's your cue.

1:02:02.887 --> 1:02:05.389
Fuck, Zwick!

1:02:05.424 --> 1:02:08.222
Doesn't anybody use
the goddamn doorbell anymore?

1:02:08.258 --> 1:02:10.257
What the hell happened to you?

1:02:10.292 --> 1:02:12.735
The guy who hit the game.

1:02:12.770 --> 1:02:14.403
The fucking psycho actually
came back,

1:02:14.438 --> 1:02:16.062
was asking about...

1:02:16.098 --> 1:02:17.163
April Reyes.

1:02:17.199 --> 1:02:18.041
You believe that?

1:02:18.076 --> 1:02:19.707
Oh yeah.

1:02:19.742 --> 1:02:22.309
You uh,
get a good look at him?

1:02:22.344 --> 1:02:24.340
Oh yeah.

1:02:24.376 --> 1:02:27.881
Some piece of shit locksmith
did a job for me

1:02:27.916 --> 1:02:30.254
over the Heavenly Arches
Development.

1:02:30.289 --> 1:02:32.185
Yeah, Miller Graham.

1:02:34.590 --> 1:02:37.124
What's with the gloves?

1:02:45.337 --> 1:02:47.902
What the fuck is this?

1:02:47.938 --> 1:02:50.866
You know it never really made
sense to me.

1:02:50.901 --> 1:02:52.574
In a way.

1:02:52.609 --> 1:02:55.103
Why am I working for you?

1:02:55.138 --> 1:02:57.105
Is this about money?

1:02:57.140 --> 1:02:58.576
I'll get you more money.

1:02:58.611 --> 1:03:00.547
Eh.

1:03:00.582 --> 1:03:02.450
I want it all.

1:03:02.485 --> 1:03:06.280
Ian, buddy...

1:03:06.315 --> 1:03:08.254
That's not very reasonable.

1:03:09.490 --> 1:03:11.323
I know.

1:03:28.637 --> 1:03:31.475
I thought you were looking
for April.

1:03:32.210 --> 1:03:33.383
What the hell happened to you?

1:03:33.418 --> 1:03:35.111
He didn't have her.

1:03:35.146 --> 1:03:37.010
But I think I know who does.

1:03:37.045 --> 1:03:38.455
Zwick.

1:03:38.490 --> 1:03:41.314
No, it's time to go to Beth.

1:03:41.349 --> 1:03:42.451
Just give her the money

1:03:42.487 --> 1:03:45.157
and hopefully she can get you
out of this.

1:03:45.192 --> 1:03:47.088
I don't think April has
that kind of time.

1:03:47.123 --> 1:03:48.497
FRANK:
Miller.

1:03:48.532 --> 1:03:50.632
We tried it your way.

1:03:50.667 --> 1:03:52.500
Your way made things worse.

1:03:52.535 --> 1:03:54.167
I know it did.

1:03:54.203 --> 1:03:56.472
But if Beth gets any closer
to Zwick on this,

1:03:56.507 --> 1:03:58.266
he's gonna kill her.

1:03:58.302 --> 1:04:00.471
We know what he's capable of.

1:04:02.579 --> 1:04:04.145
I just need to think.

1:04:12.723 --> 1:04:15.358
I think someone decided for you.

1:04:39.551 --> 1:04:40.682
You sure it's here, man?

1:04:40.718 --> 1:04:42.050
Maybe he took it home with him.

1:04:42.085 --> 1:04:44.317
No, it's here.
I'd seen him put it in the desk.

1:04:46.692 --> 1:04:47.986
He's gonna know
it was us, Hector.

1:04:48.021 --> 1:04:48.886
PEREZ:
It's alright, man.

1:04:48.921 --> 1:04:49.850
We need answers.

1:04:56.025 --> 1:05:00.228
Let's go see what that snitch
was so eager to show Stern.

1:05:00.263 --> 1:05:03.670
And this one right here.

1:05:03.706 --> 1:05:05.234
You're very good.

1:05:05.270 --> 1:05:08.402
I'll move my little horsey...

1:05:08.438 --> 1:05:11.278
Gallop, gallop, gallop, boof.

1:05:12.483 --> 1:05:13.849
She needed help.

1:05:13.884 --> 1:05:15.376
So, you helped her
with a robbery?

1:05:15.411 --> 1:05:16.344
They were gonna kill her.

1:05:16.379 --> 1:05:17.545
They probably already have.

1:05:17.580 --> 1:05:19.281
Look, I have evidence on all
of them.

1:05:19.316 --> 1:05:20.680
I can take this to the DA,

1:05:20.716 --> 1:05:21.724
but I need you
to tell me everything.

1:05:21.760 --> 1:05:23.160
And I need you to go
on record.

1:05:23.195 --> 1:05:24.261
No.

1:05:24.296 --> 1:05:25.721
Bad idea.

1:05:25.757 --> 1:05:28.090
Garrett could have half
the department in his pocket.

1:05:28.125 --> 1:05:29.091
Stern's clean.

1:05:29.126 --> 1:05:30.698
Please tell me you
didn't tell him anything.

1:05:30.733 --> 1:05:32.929
Of course, I told him.

1:05:32.964 --> 1:05:34.500
Oh, no...

1:05:34.536 --> 1:05:36.537
Well, then you gotta go to him
and convince him to drop it.

1:05:36.572 --> 1:05:37.698
Oh, what?

1:05:37.733 --> 1:05:39.601
So, you can keep taking care
of things?

1:05:39.636 --> 1:05:41.269
'Cause that's working out
real well.

1:05:41.304 --> 1:05:42.543
No, Miller, fuck it!

1:05:42.579 --> 1:05:44.280
You're out!

1:05:48.278 --> 1:05:50.018
Beth, that night.

1:05:50.053 --> 1:05:52.753
The reason why I had
to take the deal.

1:05:52.788 --> 1:05:54.547
Zwick planted that gun.

1:05:54.582 --> 1:05:56.217
What are you talking about?

1:05:56.253 --> 1:05:57.484
He murdered Kevin.

1:05:57.519 --> 1:05:59.722
I swear to God it's true.

1:06:01.125 --> 1:06:02.223
Did April know?

1:06:02.258 --> 1:06:03.224
MILLER:
No.

1:06:03.260 --> 1:06:05.398
Just me and Frank.

1:06:05.434 --> 1:06:08.263
And I couldn't tell you,
because you guys were in danger.

1:06:08.298 --> 1:06:10.966
Zwick made threats.

1:06:11.001 --> 1:06:12.471
Okay.

1:06:13.677 --> 1:06:15.876
You gotta trust me.

1:06:15.911 --> 1:06:18.281
Do you still have the money?

1:06:18.316 --> 1:06:19.449
Yeah.

1:06:19.484 --> 1:06:20.308
BETH:
Okay.

1:06:20.343 --> 1:06:21.610
It's material evidence.

1:06:21.645 --> 1:06:25.048
I can take it directly
to Stern tonight.

1:06:25.083 --> 1:06:26.286
If I cooperate,

1:06:26.321 --> 1:06:28.491
there's a lot that's gonna
come out about me.

1:06:28.527 --> 1:06:30.917
It's the only way.

1:06:30.952 --> 1:06:33.956
If you help us,
maybe we can work something out.

1:06:33.991 --> 1:06:35.830
Yeah.

1:06:35.866 --> 1:06:37.630
<i>LINSAY:</i>

1:06:37.666 --> 1:06:40.435
<i>-FRANK: </i>

1:06:54.616 --> 1:06:55.142
Bravo!

1:06:55.177 --> 1:06:56.718
Bravo!

1:06:56.753 --> 1:06:58.180
Hey, we could be a duet.

1:06:58.816 --> 1:06:59.982
Yeah.
That'd be good.

1:07:00.017 --> 1:07:00.721
Okay.

1:07:00.756 --> 1:07:01.650
It's your move.

1:07:01.685 --> 1:07:04.518
You've always had a way
with her, Frank.

1:07:04.553 --> 1:07:06.630
Even when she was a baby.

1:07:06.665 --> 1:07:09.322
Well, yeah, she's family.

1:07:09.358 --> 1:07:11.101
So are you.

1:07:13.595 --> 1:07:16.972
You be careful out there.

1:07:17.007 --> 1:07:19.168
You keep an eye
on my little girl.

1:07:59.879 --> 1:08:00.745
Hey.

1:08:00.780 --> 1:08:02.241
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>Yeah, it's done.</i>

1:08:02.277 --> 1:08:04.416
Listen I'm gonna call in some
anonymous tip to the station

1:08:04.451 --> 1:08:06.354
about a disturbance
at Garrett's house.

1:08:06.389 --> 1:08:07.755
-I need you--
-<i> JONES : Did you--</i>

1:08:07.790 --> 1:08:09.050
Listen to me!

1:08:09.086 --> 1:08:11.986
You two need to figure out a
way to plant that gun on Miller

1:08:12.021 --> 1:08:13.895
and get the money
before homicide brings him in.

1:08:13.931 --> 1:08:15.697
Didn't see my texts, did you?

1:08:15.733 --> 1:08:17.398
I didn't see what?

1:08:20.738 --> 1:08:21.903
What the fuck are these?

1:08:21.938 --> 1:08:23.630
Fisher gave 'em to Stern.

1:08:23.665 --> 1:08:24.836
There-- there's audio, too.

1:08:24.871 --> 1:08:27.607
Listen.

1:08:27.642 --> 1:08:29.369
<i>GARRETT :</i>
<i>What the hell happened here?</i>

1:08:29.405 --> 1:08:30.739
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>I caught this one</i>
<i>with half her take</i>

1:08:30.774 --> 1:08:32.040
<i>stuffed in the bottom</i>
<i>of her purse.</i>

1:08:32.076 --> 1:08:33.781
<i>GARETT :</i>
<i>So, you beat her half to deat?</i>

1:08:33.817 --> 1:08:35.708
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>You want me</i>
<i>to protect your money or not?</i>

1:08:35.744 --> 1:08:37.846
<i>GARRETT :</i>
<i>Just not the face, Zwick.</i>
<i>Why do you keep doing this?</i>

1:08:37.882 --> 1:08:38.722
<i>-She's worthless to me--</i>
Jesus, fuck!

1:08:38.757 --> 1:08:39.587
Alright, alright, alright!

1:08:39.622 --> 1:08:40.115
Alright!

1:08:40.150 --> 1:08:41.356
Enough!

1:08:42.650 --> 1:08:44.584
Stern heard this, too?

1:08:44.620 --> 1:08:46.728
<i>JONES :</i>
<i>It was on a drive that</i>
<i>we pulled from his desk drawe.</i>

1:08:46.763 --> 1:08:49.257
Motherfucker!

1:08:49.293 --> 1:08:51.531
Goddamn it!

1:08:54.799 --> 1:08:57.372
That snake Garrett was
cooperating with Fisher.

1:08:57.408 --> 1:09:01.736
I told you we should have
taken him out months ago!

1:09:01.771 --> 1:09:02.779
<i>JONES :</i>
<i>What do we do?</i>

1:09:02.814 --> 1:09:03.738
Well, if Stern's heard this,

1:09:03.774 --> 1:09:05.347
so it's a little too late,
isn't it?

1:09:06.781 --> 1:09:07.841
Okay.

1:09:07.877 --> 1:09:10.279
So, uh, you two get over
to Frank's shop.

1:09:10.314 --> 1:09:11.485
Grab the cash.

1:09:11.521 --> 1:09:13.481
Kill Miller if you have to,
but I don't give a fuck.

1:09:13.516 --> 1:09:14.483
Kill anybody, alright.

1:09:14.518 --> 1:09:18.695
Just grab the fucking money.

1:09:18.730 --> 1:09:20.328
We're gonna need it.

1:09:20.364 --> 1:09:23.123
Meet back here at the motel
when you're done.

1:09:24.268 --> 1:09:25.801
You said that after we took
care of Garrett,

1:09:25.836 --> 1:09:26.803
the money was mine.

1:09:26.838 --> 1:09:29.096
Yeah, well, plans change.

1:09:29.131 --> 1:09:30.966
And If you want to see so much
as a fucking dollar,

1:09:31.002 --> 1:09:33.408
you'll help me make sure Perez
and Jones get Miller.

1:09:36.138 --> 1:09:38.247
<i>VIVIAN :</i>
<i>So, you're a private detective?</i>

1:09:38.283 --> 1:09:40.116
<i>I didn't know they existed</i>
<i>except in books.</i>

1:09:40.152 --> 1:09:41.515
<i>Or else they were</i>
<i>greasy little men...</i>

1:09:47.292 --> 1:09:48.984
<i>MARLOWE :</i>
<i>I'm not very tall either.</i>

1:09:49.019 --> 1:09:51.058
<i>Next time I'll come on stilts,</i>
<i>wear a white tie,</i>

1:09:51.093 --> 1:09:52.591
<i>and carry a tennis racket.</i>

1:09:52.627 --> 1:09:54.187
<i>VIVIAN :</i>
<i>I doubt if even that would help.</i>

1:09:56.834 --> 1:09:58.167
Frank's Locksmith Co.

1:09:58.203 --> 1:09:59.467
<i>APRIL :</i>
<i>Miller, it's April.</i>

1:10:00.730 --> 1:10:02.328
Where the hell have you been?

1:10:02.363 --> 1:10:03.664
-I've been calling--
-<i> APRIL : It's April.</i>

1:10:03.699 --> 1:10:04.497
<i>Can you hear me? Miller?</i>

1:10:04.533 --> 1:10:05.070
Yes, April.

1:10:05.105 --> 1:10:06.133
I can hear you.

1:10:10.382 --> 1:10:11.239
-Daddy!
-Frank! Get her!

1:10:11.274 --> 1:10:11.908
Lindsay!

1:10:13.410 --> 1:10:14.078
Get down here.

1:10:14.113 --> 1:10:15.043
Be quiet.

1:10:35.837 --> 1:10:38.334
JONES:
Give up the money, Miller,
this can all go away.

1:10:38.369 --> 1:10:39.903
It's not here.

1:10:44.279 --> 1:10:45.572
Frank, where's the other guy?

1:10:45.607 --> 1:10:46.580
There's another?

1:10:50.247 --> 1:10:52.388
Frank!

1:10:53.417 --> 1:10:54.456
LINDSAY:
Daddy!

1:10:57.862 --> 1:10:59.923
It's over, Miller.

1:11:01.257 --> 1:11:02.389
<i>DISPATCH OFFICER 2 :</i>
<i>All units. All units.</i>

1:11:02.424 --> 1:11:05.161
<i>A shooting just occurred</i>
<i>at 457 Monte Vista Avenue.</i>

1:11:05.196 --> 1:11:06.296
Shit!

1:11:06.331 --> 1:11:06.798
<i>DISPATCH OFFICER 2 :</i>
<i>Multiple shots fired.</i>

1:11:07.862 --> 1:11:09.570
-Daddy, help me.
-Shut up!

1:11:10.875 --> 1:11:13.039
Where's the money?

1:11:13.074 --> 1:11:15.545
It's not here.

1:11:15.580 --> 1:11:16.439
Please.

1:11:16.474 --> 1:11:17.440
PEREZ:
Where is it?

1:11:17.475 --> 1:11:18.341
MILLER:
Beth has it.

1:11:18.376 --> 1:11:20.541
She's driving it
to Stern's right now.

1:11:20.576 --> 1:11:22.116
Daddy, help me!

1:11:22.151 --> 1:11:23.444
It's gonna be okay, Lindsay.

1:11:23.479 --> 1:11:24.754
I promise.

1:11:24.789 --> 1:11:25.748
For your sake,

1:11:25.783 --> 1:11:26.615
you better hope she brings
it back.

1:11:26.651 --> 1:11:28.054
Please, man.
I'm begging you.

1:11:28.089 --> 1:11:29.022
I'm begging you.

1:11:32.058 --> 1:11:32.793
Lindsay!

1:11:32.828 --> 1:11:33.629
Lindsay!

1:11:33.664 --> 1:11:35.255
Lindsay!

1:11:52.617 --> 1:11:53.449
Frank!

1:11:56.954 --> 1:11:58.921
Frank, you still here?

1:12:17.372 --> 1:12:19.408
-Beth, they took her.
-No!

1:12:19.443 --> 1:12:21.008
-But we're gonna get her back!
-No, no, no, no.

1:12:21.043 --> 1:12:22.912
No, no, no...

1:12:22.947 --> 1:12:23.813
Whose blood is that?

1:12:23.848 --> 1:12:24.439
It's Frank's,

1:12:24.474 --> 1:12:25.241
He's dead.

1:12:25.276 --> 1:12:26.441
Frank?

1:12:26.476 --> 1:12:27.313
He's dead?

1:12:27.349 --> 1:12:28.313
How could you let this happen?

1:12:28.348 --> 1:12:29.247
It's April's fault.

1:12:29.282 --> 1:12:30.952
She's working with them
and they took her.

1:12:30.987 --> 1:12:31.713
No.

1:12:31.748 --> 1:12:32.982
All they want is the money.

1:12:33.018 --> 1:12:34.347
We get the money to them,
they'll let her go.

1:12:37.691 --> 1:12:39.019
<i>ZWICK :</i>
<i>You got my money?</i>

1:12:39.054 --> 1:12:39.896
<i>MILLER :</i>
<i>I have it.</i>

1:12:39.931 --> 1:12:41.022
<i>Where do I meet you?</i>

1:12:41.057 --> 1:12:44.460
Abandoned stone yard
off Lohman Avenue.

1:12:44.496 --> 1:12:46.661
You can't miss it.

1:12:46.696 --> 1:12:48.262
You can't afford to.

1:12:51.734 --> 1:12:52.709
We're gonna get her.

1:12:52.744 --> 1:12:53.610
Oh my God.

1:12:53.645 --> 1:12:54.675
I promise you,
we're gonna get her back.

1:13:14.194 --> 1:13:16.163
Handcuffs?

1:13:16.198 --> 1:13:17.459
That's a nice touch.

1:13:17.494 --> 1:13:18.991
She's 12.

1:13:19.026 --> 1:13:21.130
Yeah, well, you never know.

1:13:22.973 --> 1:13:25.332
Wait, Jones?

1:13:31.841 --> 1:13:34.081
Got you a little present.

1:14:06.050 --> 1:14:07.915
Where are you going?

1:14:07.950 --> 1:14:09.752
Huh?

1:14:09.787 --> 1:14:10.652
Hey!

1:14:15.191 --> 1:14:17.190
What the fuck is this?

1:14:17.226 --> 1:14:18.050
She's just a kid.

1:14:18.086 --> 1:14:20.228
This was never part of the plan.

1:14:20.263 --> 1:14:21.095
You want to get out of here?

1:14:21.131 --> 1:14:23.159
We need leverage.

1:14:24.167 --> 1:14:25.760
God, you make me sick.

1:14:25.795 --> 1:14:27.094
Oh, don't be so naive.

1:14:27.130 --> 1:14:29.506
You knew what
you were getting into.

1:14:56.265 --> 1:14:58.029
I'm going for a smoke.

1:15:19.146 --> 1:15:21.151
MILLER:
Hey, look at this.

1:15:23.854 --> 1:15:25.518
BETH:
Day's End Motel.

1:15:25.554 --> 1:15:27.929
That's down the street
from where you're meeting Zwick.

1:15:27.964 --> 1:15:28.658
Alright.

1:15:28.693 --> 1:15:29.762
So, you go get Lindsay.

1:15:29.797 --> 1:15:31.592
I'll try to stall Zwick
as long as I can.

1:15:31.627 --> 1:15:32.459
No.

1:15:32.495 --> 1:15:33.531
April is the one who got
Lindsay taken

1:15:33.566 --> 1:15:34.334
in the first place.

1:15:34.369 --> 1:15:35.664
We can't trust her.

1:15:35.700 --> 1:15:37.132
She was after me.

1:15:37.167 --> 1:15:39.037
She didn't even know
Lindsay was there.

1:15:41.578 --> 1:15:44.339
Zwick has no reason
to keep you alive.

1:15:45.616 --> 1:15:48.541
If you can save Lindsay,
it's all that matters.

1:15:57.355 --> 1:15:59.992
You haven't heard anything
about that bomb, have you?

1:16:02.559 --> 1:16:04.459
<i>ACTRESS ON TV:</i>
<i>That happened on</i>
<i>your side of the border.</i>

1:16:04.495 --> 1:16:08.235
<i>ACTOR ON TV:</i>
<i>In a place like this</i>
<i>you hear things.</i>

1:16:08.737 --> 1:16:11.063
<i>ACTRESS ON TV:</i>
<i>I heard the explosion.</i>

1:16:11.099 --> 1:16:13.038
<i>ACTOR ON TV:</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

1:16:14.168 --> 1:16:16.903
<i>Well, this case is over.</i>

1:16:56.781 --> 1:16:58.382
Easy now, Miller.

1:16:58.417 --> 1:16:59.078
Easy.

1:16:59.113 --> 1:17:00.221
Where's my daughter?

1:17:00.256 --> 1:17:01.147
ZWICK:
Nearby.

1:17:01.182 --> 1:17:03.054
Don't do anything stupid.

1:17:03.089 --> 1:17:05.851
You hand her over to me,
and the money's yours.

1:17:05.886 --> 1:17:06.859
Yeah.

1:17:06.894 --> 1:17:08.087
I think you got your order
of operations

1:17:08.122 --> 1:17:09.457
all fucked up there.

1:17:11.800 --> 1:17:15.103
How do I know you're not gonna
kill me?

1:17:15.138 --> 1:17:17.740
You don't.

1:17:23.147 --> 1:17:25.247
<i>MIKE :</i>
<i>Does your intuition</i>
<i>also tell you about my wife?</i>

1:17:25.283 --> 1:17:26.649
<i>ADAIR :</i>
<i>Wife?</i>

1:17:26.684 --> 1:17:28.445
<i>MIKE :</i>
<i>She was accosted on the street</i>
<i>a little while ago</i>

1:17:28.480 --> 1:17:31.547
<i>and led across to some dive</i>
<i>on your side of the border.</i>

1:17:31.582 --> 1:17:32.980
<i>Hmm.</i>

1:17:33.015 --> 1:17:34.385
<i>The Vargas family</i>

1:17:34.420 --> 1:17:36.792
<i>seems to be getting into</i>
<i>quite a lot of trouble tonigh.</i>

1:17:39.121 --> 1:17:40.161
<i>Can you describe this man?</i>

1:17:40.197 --> 1:17:41.323
<i>A little.</i>

1:17:41.358 --> 1:17:42.627
<i>MIKE :</i>
<i>Well, the first one seems...</i>

1:17:46.027 --> 1:17:46.961
<i>Not exactly.</i>

1:17:51.338 --> 1:17:52.709
April?

1:17:53.835 --> 1:17:54.438
April?

1:17:54.473 --> 1:17:55.305
Zwick?

1:18:00.611 --> 1:18:01.116
Come on.

1:18:01.151 --> 1:18:02.184
Let's go.

1:18:02.219 --> 1:18:04.285
Get the money.

1:18:04.320 --> 1:18:04.813
It's in here.

1:18:04.849 --> 1:18:06.316
Well, get it out.

1:18:08.718 --> 1:18:09.290
Come on.

1:18:09.325 --> 1:18:10.423
Quit stalling.

1:18:10.458 --> 1:18:11.483
One phone call,

1:18:11.519 --> 1:18:12.458
we'll be talking
about your little girl

1:18:12.494 --> 1:18:13.659
in the past tense.

1:18:13.695 --> 1:18:15.655
I got shot in the leg, asshole!

1:18:19.828 --> 1:18:21.698
April!

1:18:21.733 --> 1:18:22.997
Where you at?

1:18:29.344 --> 1:18:30.202
Let's go.

1:18:30.237 --> 1:18:31.644
Throw the gun over here.

1:18:31.680 --> 1:18:32.678
You think I'm a fucking idiot?

1:18:32.714 --> 1:18:34.341
I think you're out of options.

1:18:34.376 --> 1:18:36.010
I think we're both out
of options.

1:18:36.045 --> 1:18:37.082
Stern knows everything.

1:18:37.118 --> 1:18:40.114
I will make this phone call
right fucking now.

1:18:40.149 --> 1:18:41.923
Throw that gun over here.

1:18:44.094 --> 1:18:45.861
Okay.

1:18:54.898 --> 1:18:55.730
There you go.

1:18:55.765 --> 1:18:57.205
Finally.

1:18:57.241 --> 1:18:57.899
No, no, no.

1:18:57.935 --> 1:18:58.837
Put your hands up.

1:18:58.872 --> 1:18:59.802
Up-- up where I can see 'em.

1:18:59.838 --> 1:19:00.670
Come on, come on.

1:19:33.035 --> 1:19:34.903
PEREZ:
April?

1:19:44.781 --> 1:19:45.385
Hey!

1:19:45.420 --> 1:19:46.254
Kid, stop!

1:19:46.289 --> 1:19:47.714
Come back!

1:19:49.819 --> 1:19:50.885
Lindsay!

1:19:50.920 --> 1:19:51.690
Come here.

1:19:51.726 --> 1:19:53.429
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

1:19:53.464 --> 1:19:54.360
-Are you okay?
-I'm okay.

1:19:54.395 --> 1:19:55.561
Okay.

1:19:55.597 --> 1:19:56.958
Stay close to me.

1:19:56.994 --> 1:19:58.359
Yeah, super tight.

1:19:58.395 --> 1:20:00.236
Now, I need you
to sit down here, baby.

1:20:00.271 --> 1:20:01.127
Close your eyes.

1:20:01.162 --> 1:20:01.962
Close your eyes.

1:20:10.172 --> 1:20:12.271
Lindsay, stand up, baby.

1:20:12.306 --> 1:20:13.414
Okay, come with me.

1:20:13.450 --> 1:20:14.545
You see that car?

1:20:14.580 --> 1:20:14.974
Yeah.

1:20:15.009 --> 1:20:15.708
Okay.

1:20:15.744 --> 1:20:16.712
-We need to get into it.
-Okay.

1:20:16.747 --> 1:20:18.184
Okay?

1:20:24.493 --> 1:20:25.592
Get down, baby.

1:20:25.627 --> 1:20:26.956
Where are we going, mom?

1:20:26.991 --> 1:20:28.491
To save your father.

1:20:42.845 --> 1:20:46.344
How'd you convince April
to do this?

1:20:48.979 --> 1:20:51.848
Ah, Miller.

1:20:51.883 --> 1:20:54.521
It was her idea.

1:20:54.556 --> 1:20:57.416
You're lying.

1:20:57.451 --> 1:20:58.991
Why would she work with you?

1:20:59.027 --> 1:21:03.596
Well, we do have one thing
in common.

1:21:03.632 --> 1:21:05.165
We both hate you.

1:21:07.235 --> 1:21:10.297
Lock the doors behind me
and don't let anyone in here

1:21:10.332 --> 1:21:11.833
either than me or your dad.

1:21:11.868 --> 1:21:13.309
Okay?

1:21:30.419 --> 1:21:32.284
And then faking her kidnapping.

1:21:32.320 --> 1:21:33.054
Ah, there you go.

1:21:33.089 --> 1:21:34.486
That was genius.

1:21:34.521 --> 1:21:37.191
Led you straight to Garrett.

1:21:37.226 --> 1:21:39.529
Oh, you haven't heard?

1:21:43.605 --> 1:21:46.573
Garrett's dead.

1:21:46.608 --> 1:21:48.703
You killed him.

1:21:55.585 --> 1:21:57.751
That's right Miller.

1:21:57.787 --> 1:22:01.413
She would keep all that money.

1:22:01.448 --> 1:22:03.784
And I will take over.

1:22:04.626 --> 1:22:07.088
But here we are.

1:22:28.512 --> 1:22:32.277
I never believed
what you said about Kevin.

1:22:32.313 --> 1:22:35.649
But April...

1:22:35.685 --> 1:22:37.785
My brother wouldn't
pull a gun on anyone.

1:22:40.121 --> 1:22:43.131
No.

1:22:46.327 --> 1:22:47.896
Jesus Christ.

1:22:47.931 --> 1:22:49.830
April.

1:22:52.400 --> 1:22:55.710
I thought that you...

1:22:55.745 --> 1:22:57.475
You thought what, Miller?

1:22:59.016 --> 1:23:00.574
Zwick might have pulled
the trigger that night,

1:23:00.610 --> 1:23:01.583
but Kevin never would
have been there

1:23:01.618 --> 1:23:03.184
if it weren't for you.

1:23:08.823 --> 1:23:11.894
And now you get to walk?

1:23:11.929 --> 1:23:15.891
You get to start over
and have a family.

1:23:15.926 --> 1:23:17.523
Come on.

1:23:17.558 --> 1:23:19.094
You don't have to do this.

1:23:19.130 --> 1:23:23.704
I want to do this.

1:23:23.739 --> 1:23:25.599
You and the monster

1:23:25.635 --> 1:23:26.806
that murdered my brother
kill each other

1:23:26.841 --> 1:23:29.512
in a pile of rocks.

1:23:29.547 --> 1:23:30.871
That's what happens.

1:23:32.109 --> 1:23:34.380
BETH:
April!

1:23:35.212 --> 1:23:37.548
Put the gun down.

1:23:38.313 --> 1:23:40.122
Put it down.

1:23:42.385 --> 1:23:45.694
You helped us find Lindsay.

1:23:45.729 --> 1:23:47.987
You've done a good thing.

1:23:48.828 --> 1:23:49.660
I'm sorry.

1:23:49.696 --> 1:23:51.366
I never meant
to get Lindsay involved.

1:23:51.401 --> 1:23:52.426
I know.

1:23:52.462 --> 1:23:54.529
MILLER:
April, you're right.

1:23:54.564 --> 1:23:57.363
I did get Kevin killed
that night.

1:23:57.398 --> 1:23:58.866
It was my fault.

1:23:58.901 --> 1:24:03.502
And I thought about it everyday
for the last 10 years.

1:24:03.537 --> 1:24:05.576
He was my best friend.

1:24:07.576 --> 1:24:09.617
I can't change what happened.

1:24:09.652 --> 1:24:11.183
I wish I could.

1:24:11.218 --> 1:24:15.722
And I know
I fucked everything up.

1:24:15.757 --> 1:24:17.658
Including you.

1:24:17.693 --> 1:24:19.361
And I'm sorry.

1:25:44.981 --> 1:25:47.407
SHARON:
Two jobs, Mr. Graham.

1:25:47.442 --> 1:25:49.710
I'm impressed.

1:25:49.745 --> 1:25:52.119
Your employers speak highly
of you.

1:25:52.154 --> 1:25:54.787
Gotta get that
college fund started.

1:25:54.823 --> 1:25:56.687
How is she?

1:25:59.921 --> 1:26:04.158
There's uh, good days
and bad days.

1:26:04.193 --> 1:26:05.833
Mhmmm.

1:26:05.868 --> 1:26:08.727
It's gonna take time.

1:26:08.762 --> 1:26:11.673
But she's gonna be alright.

1:26:11.708 --> 1:26:14.601
Yeah, I hope so.

1:26:14.636 --> 1:26:16.707
STERN:
Detective Fisher.

1:26:20.715 --> 1:26:21.777
Chief?

1:26:21.813 --> 1:26:22.842
Well, there'll be more pomp
and circumstance,

1:26:22.877 --> 1:26:26.046
but figured
I should tell you now.

1:26:32.753 --> 1:26:35.462
Congratulations, Lieutenant.

1:26:37.326 --> 1:26:39.866
Thank you.
